BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, April 15 (YONHAP) -- South Korea on Friday 
officially denied press reports that it has consulted with China 
on signing a bilateral friendship treaty. Responding to press 
reports that Seoul offered to sign the pact at ongoing policy 
planning talks in Beijing, Foreign Ministry spokesman Chang 
Ki-ho said, "the proposal was made just as an idea and it cannot 
be considered that we had any talks or consultations with 
Beijing on the matter." 
  The press had reported that Seoul proposed signing the 
treaty 
at the Beijing talks which opened Wednesday and that China 
responded positively to the offer. 

